                "INSTRUCTIONS TO APPLICANTS\nAll the above-mentioned positions are permanent, and the appointment will be done in terms of section 47 of the Protection of Personal Information Act 4 of 2013 (POPIA) as the enabling Act.\nA comprehensive CV should be accompanied by the Employment Application Form downloadable from the BMA website (www.bma.gov.za).\nApplications must be emailed to the specified email addresses above, hand or mail delivered to the Border Management Authority, Branch: Human Capital Management, Government Communication, and Information System Building, Tshedimosetso House, 1035 cnr Francis Baard and Festive streets, Hatfield, Pretoria, 0083.\nOnly shortlisted candidates will be required to submit certified copies of their qualifications. Should a candidate have foreign qualification(s), such must be accompanied by an evaluation certificate obtained from the South African Qualifications Authority (SAQA) to confirm the appropriate National Qualifications Framework (NQF) Level.\nApplication form should be completed in full (e.g. reference number).\nFailure to comply with any of the above instructions may result in the application being disqualified.\nApplications received after the closing date will not be considered.\nIf you are not contacted after three months of the closing date, consider your application unsuccessful.\nBMA reserves the right to fill or not to fill these positions.\nAll enquiries may be sent to: recruit.enquiries@bma.gov.za.\n \nBMA Job Application form\n \nTHE CLOSING DATE FOR ALL APPLICATIONS ABOVE IS 24 NOVEMBER 2023 @ 16h00."
