            "content": [
                " \nCOMMISSION FOR CONCILIATION, MEDIATION AND ARBITRATION (CCMA) \n ",
                " \n \nCASE MANAGEMENT OFFICER\nKwa-Zulu Natal Province \u2013 Pietermaritzburg Office\nREF: CMOPMB11-23\nPost level:09\n \nThe Kwa-Zulu Natal Province \u2013 Pietermaritzburg Office has a vacancy of Case Management Officer.\n \nPurpose\nTo effectively and efficiently handle queries and assist the public with regard to appropriate processing procedures, screening of cases in terms of relevant legislation and CCMA guidelines.\n \nKey Performance Areas:-\n\u2022 Case Advice\n\u2022 Case Screening\n\u2022 Case Capturing\n\u2022 Schedule and screen documentation\n\u2022 Process outcome and finalise cases\n\u2022 Venue Administration\n\u2022 Pre-Conciliation\n \nKey Requirements:\n\u2022 Unless a candidate can demonstrate suitability through relevant experience of not less than three (3) years in Employment Laws, Trade Union environment/Bargaining Council/Labour Inspector or Human Resources role, a Matric and Diploma in Labour Relations (or relevant equivalent) with one (1) year of practical experience will be required\n\u2022 One (1) to three (3) years relevant working experience in a case management service Employment Laws, Trade Union environment/Bargaining Council/Labour Inspector or Human Resources role\n\u2022 At least 2 African languages would be an advantage\n \n \nClosing date: 21 November 2023\n\nTo respond in confidence, please send your detailed CV, copies of your qualifications, and a covering letter disclosing information that will assist the panel in considering your application to: recruitmentkzn@ccma.org.za\n \nWhen responding to the advert please ensure that the position reference Ref: CMOPMB11-23 is quoted first on the subject line, as is. And that the application is sent to the email address contained herein. Failure to observe this protocol may result in your application being disqualified\u201d.\n \nIf we have not responded within a Month from the closing date, you should regard your application as unsuccessful. Correspondence will only be entered into with short-listed candidates. The CCMA reserves the right not to make an appointment. It is the intention of the CCMA to promote representativity in respect of race, gender and disability through the filling of the posts.\nPreference will be given to candidate from the designated groups.\n \n \n \n ",
                " \n \n \n \nADMINISTRATION: CLERK\nGauteng Province \u2013 Johannesburg Office\nRef: ACJHB11-23\nPost level: 12\nThe Gauteng Province (Johannesburg Office) has a vacancy for an Administration Clerk.\n\nPurpose: Monitor that all equipment and assets are in working order and provide the necessary administrative support services to CCMA staff to enable them to achieve their objectives.\n\nKey Performance Areas:-\n\u2022 Stock Management\n\u2022 Office Management.\n\u2022 Access control\n\u2022 Building Maintenance\n\nKey Requirements:\n\u2022 Grade 12- and 1-year administration certificate.\n\u2022 1 year\u2019s administration experience in an Office or Administration environment and handyman experience.\n \n\nClosing date: 21 November 2023\n\nTo respond in confidence, please send your detailed CV, copy of your qualifications, and a covering letter disclosing information that will assist the panel in considering your application to: recruitmentjhb@ccma.org.za\n\n\n\u201cWhen responding to the advert please ensure that the position reference Ref: ACJHB11-23 is quoted first on the subject line, as is. Failure to observe this protocol may result in your application being disqualified.\u201d\n\nIf we have not responded within a Month from the closing date, you should regard your application as unsuccessful. Correspondence will only be entered into with short-listed candidates. The CCMA reserves the right not to make an appointment. It is the intention of the CCMA to promote representivity in respect of race, gender and disability through the filling of the posts. Preference will be given to candidate from the designated groups.",
                "ASSISTANT MANAGER: ACQUISITION MANAGEMENT (RE-ADVERTISEMENT)\nNational Office\nRef: AMAM11-23\nPost level:6\n \nThe Finance, Supply Chain Management department has a vacancy of an Assistant Manager: Acquisition Management.\n\nPurpose\nTo facilitate the acquisition process in the procurement of goods and services for the CCMA in compliance with Supply Chain Management Policies and Procedures.\n\nKey Performance Areas: \u2013\n\u2022 Sourcing Process Management\n\u2022 Bid Process Management\n\u2022 Supply Chain Management Compliance\n\u2022 Supplier Performance Monitoring\n\u2022 Reporting\n\u2022 Team Supervision\n\nKey Requirements:\n\u2022 National Diploma in Supply Chain Management or equivalent.\n\u2022 5 years\u2019 experience in supply chain management, of which 2 years is a supervisory level.\n \n \nClosing date: 16 November 2023\n \nTo respond in confidence, please send your detailed CV, copy of your qualifications, and a covering letter disclosing information that will assist the panel in considering your application to: recruitment@ccma.org.za. \n \n\u201cWhen responding to the advert please ensure that the position reference Ref: AMAM11-23 is quoted first on the subject line, as is. And that the application is sent to the email address contained herein. Failure to observe this protocol may result in your application being disqualified\u201d.\n \nNB: This is a re-advertisement, applicants who had previously applied need to re-apply as the content of the advert has changed. If we have not responded within a Month from the closing date, you should regard your application as unsuccessful. Correspondence will only be entered into with short-listed candidates. \n \nThe CCMA reserves the right not to make an appointment. It is the intention of the CCMA to promote representativity in respect of race, gender and disability through the filling of the posts. Preference will be given to candidate from the designated groups."
            ],
